Governor Bala Muhammed of Bauchi State has approved the voluntary resignation of the Chief of Staff to Government House Bauchi, Alhaji Abubakar Kari. A statement signed by the Secretary to the Bauchi State Government, Sabiu Baba, said the Governor has also approved with immediate effect the appointment of Ladan Salihu, a former Director General of the Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) as the chief of staff. Until his appointment, Salihu was the Commissioner of Information and Communication. Kari resigns, Salihu takes over as Bauchi governor's Chief of Staff Gov. Mohammed appoints SSG, Chief of Staff, others Governor Mohammed swears in SSG, Chief of Staff, others